    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>You&#8217;ve taken me right back there&#8230;</></>I was lucky enough to do an exchange to Lyon when I was 16. I stayed with a family in Sainte Foy for 6 weeks. They didn&#8217;t have much money and lived four to a 2 bedroom flat, but boy did they eat well. Every dinner had an entree, main, dessert and cheese, and I found myself writing down what we ate every day so I could try to replicate it when I came home. It was here that I discovered endives, maches, creme de marron, racqlette  (?) and scoops of blackcurrant sorbet in alcohol for an apertif!</></>Each dish you pictured had such familiarity to me that I almost cried. You are a food writer extraordinaire and have bumped Lyon right to the top of my itchy feet list, again! Thank you.</p>
