      <a href="index.html?p=1478#comment-5922"><time class="comment-time" datetime="2007-05-11T10:51:00-04:00">Friday, May 11, 2007 at 10:51 am</time></a>    </header>

    
    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>The thick bottomed bottle in your fourth photo is a bouteille Lyonnaise, it is typical for the region and though you find some in Paris, they are native to Lyon and are often used to serve tap water. My grandmother lived in Lyon for many years and though I am vegetarian now, I am glad I got to sample regional cooking when I was a girl.</p>
    </div>

