    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>One of my all time favorite dining experiences was eating in Lyon &#8211; and yes, my friend and I also tried the boudin noir that time and it was heavenly, especially with the apples. Most times I tell people about that experience though, the mere thought of eating that, makes them recoil in disgust. Oh well. Oh and the traboules &#8211; how incredible are those things? I had a great time trying to find them all over the city!  Did you, by chance get to go to the Basilica &#8211; from which, on a clear day, you can see Mont Blanc?</p>
